   webmscore is a WebAssembly build of MuseScore 1.x's score-handling
   core (libmscore). MuseScore 1.x is GPL v3; the bundled WASM
   inherits that license.

   When a user imports a MIDI file, the app loads this bundle at
   runtime via the JS bridge in js/webmscore-bridge.js. The resulting
   combined work for that session is subject to GPL v3 obligations
   (source disclosure, copyleft on derivative works, etc.). A user who
   never imports a MIDI file never executes the GPL v3 code.

   The full GPL v3 text ships with the WASM bundle. A copy is
   available at: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt

   To use midi-graph without invoking GPL v3, remove the
   vendor/webmscore/ directory and the <script type="module"> tag
   that loads js/webmscore-bridge.js from index.html. The hand-rolled
   MusicXML synth in js/musicxml.js will then take over.


